  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The hypothesis of this study is that total knee alignment will be improved by preoperative
      planning from CT scans and the production of custom instruments compared to the use of
      standard instruments.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients will be randomized to have either customized knee instruments or standard generic
      instrumentation for primary total knee replacement. Postoperative CT scan will be used to
      determine alignment of each group.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
